entries.title: Elgato's Wave Link 2.0 promises clear vocals in any environment
entries.snippet:
Elgato has released Wave Link 2.0, an upgraded version of its audio stream control software, featuring advanced AI-powered voice enhancements powered by a partnership with AIcoustics. One of the key new features is "Voice Focus," which removes background noise and corrects acoustic issues to deliver professional-quality vocals regardless of the recording environment. The software supports custom audio effects and plugins but requires Elgato's compatible hardware such as microphones or the Stream Deck Plus. 

Wave Link 2.0 now takes control over the entire Windows audio system, allowing users to redirect audio to specific apps, split audio between personal and audience channels, and group apps into input channels. It also introduces intuitive volume controls through Elgato's Stream Deck ecosystem, including the ability to add volume sliders to multiple buttons and use foot pads and dials for smoother real-time control. The update is now available for download and aims to improve the workflow of content creators by integrating low-latency audio management tools and customization options.

entries.title: VALL-E
Claude's voice mode is now free for everyone - here's how to try it
entries.snippet:
Anthropic has introduced a free voice mode for its popular AI chatbot, Claude, accessible via its iOS and Android mobile apps. This new feature allows users to have spoken conversations with Claude, who responds audibly while also displaying key points on the screen. The voice mode supports five distinct voice styles—Buttery, Airy, Mellow, Glassy, and Rounded—and is currently available in English only.

Users can activate the feature by tapping the sound wave icon in the app and selecting their preferred voice. It is particularly useful in hands-free situations, such as commuting, cooking, or multitasking. To enhance the experience, it’s recommended to use the feature in quieter settings, speak naturally, and divide complex queries into smaller parts. Users can seamlessly switch between voice and text while maintaining conversation context. While similar to voice features in ChatGPT and Gemini Live, Claude’s voice mode stands out by being free for short sessions.

entries.title: Holly Herndon's AI Deepfake "Twin" Holly+ Transforms Any Song Into a Holly Herndon Song
entries.snippet:
Holly Herndon, an artist known for integrating AI into music, has unveiled Holly+, an AI deepfake "twin" that transforms any polyphonic audio into a rendition sung in Herndon's voice. This voice instrument is accessible via a website where users can upload songs and receive transformed versions. Herndon emphasizes the importance of balancing artist protection with the creative possibilities of new AI technologies. The project represents a move toward communal voice ownership, acknowledging that vocal expression is inherently shared and interpretative.

Holly+ is managed by a Decentralized Autonomous Organization (DAO), with profits from licensing and usage funding further development. Additionally, the DAO plans to launch an auction platform to sell officially approved artworks using Holly+ in partnership with Zora protocol’s Auction House. The initiative opens discussions on the future of vocal rights and artistic collaboration in the AI era.

Michael Caine and Matthew McConaughey partner with ElevenLabs for AI voice cloning
entries.snippet: Oscar-winning actors Michael Caine and Matthew McConaughey have partnered with voice-cloning startup ElevenLabs, allowing the company to replicate their voices using AI technology. Caine praised the collaboration as a way to celebrate, rather than replace, humanity by enhancing storytelling capabilities. McConaughey, a long-time supporter and investor in ElevenLabs, noted that the partnership will also let him deliver content like his newsletter in Spanish. Founded in 2022, New York-based ElevenLabs originally developed its technology for voice dubbing in media, aiming to preserve speaker identity and emotions across languages. Despite its innovations, the company faced misuse issues, including a widely publicized incident where its software was used to impersonate President Joe Biden in a robocall. In response, ElevenLabs introduced stricter security measures and now blocks unauthorized cloning of celebrity voices.

entries.title: "Metamorph isn't about replacing the human voice - it's about expanding what's possible when human creativity meets responsible AI": Antares unveils MetaMorph voice modelling plugin
entries.snippet:
Antares Audio Technologies, known for its AutoTune software, has launched a new AI-powered vocal modelling plugin called MetaMorph. This tool allows users to transform the timbre of a vocal performance using one of 12 ethically trained voice models, all based on real, compensated artists. MetaMorph operates locally without requiring cloud processing and enables a wide range of creative uses, such as simulating other singers’ voices or experimenting with non-vocal audio. Six additional voice models are available through integration with the AI voice platform Voice-Swap.

Unlike competitors such as IK Multimedia's ReSing and Dreamtonics' Vocoflex, MetaMorph does not yet allow users to create custom voice models. Antares emphasizes that MetaMorph is designed to complement, not replace, the human voice, reinforcing its commitment to ethical AI music development. The release aligns with their broader stance on responsible AI use in music creation, backed by a signed industry agreement. MetaMorph is priced at $200, with an introductory Black Friday sale offering up to 60% off, including 50% off MetaMorph and the newly updated AutoTune 2026.
